################################################################################
# AI JOB WEB APP — MASTER PROJECT OVERVIEW
# AI-Based Recruitment & Skill-Matching Platform
# Complete MVP Roadmap & Implementation Guide
################################################################################

## WHAT IS THIS PROJECT?
An AI-powered recruitment platform that automates resume screening, candidate-job
matching, and shortlisting. Recruiters post jobs; job seekers upload resumes; the AI
automatically ranks candidates by relevance. Inspired by LinkedIn + Instahyre + AI.

## TECH STACK SUMMARY
  Frontend  : React.js (Vite) + Tailwind CSS + SCSS + Material UI → http://localhost:4000
  Backend   : Node.js + Express.js → http://localhost:5000
  AI Engine : Node.js AI service using OpenAI Node.js SDK (GPT-4o-mini)
  Database  : MongoDB (Mongoose ODM) + Bull + Redis (async job queue)
  Storage   : AWS S3 / Cloudinary (resumes, avatars, logos)
  Email     : Resend API / Nodemailer

## DOMAIN & HOSTING
  Domain      : .com / .in / .tech → ₹1,900 (Namecheap/GoDaddy)
  Frontend    : Vercel (free tier — connect GitHub repo, auto-deploy)
  Backend     : Render.com (Web Service — Node.js, auto-deploy from GitHub)

## USER ROLES (from image reference)
  1. Job Seeker (User)  → Signs up/logs in as "user"
  2. Recruiter          → Signs up/logs in as "recruiter"

## SITE MAP (from image reference)
  Landing Page (public):
    ├── /          → Home (Jobs, About, Features, Testimonials, Footer)
    ├── /login     → Login (choose: Job Seeker OR Recruiter)
    └── /signup    → Signup (choose: Job Seeker OR Recruiter)

  User Dashboard (protected, role: user):
    ├── /dashboard/profile   → Profile & Settings
    ├── /dashboard/resume    → Upload & View Resume + AI Analysis
    ├── /dashboard/jobs      → Browse & Apply to Jobs
    ├── /dashboard/applied   → Track Application Statuses
    └── /dashboard/history   → Viewed/Saved Jobs History

  Recruiter Dashboard (protected, role: recruiter):
    ├── /recruiter/overview    → Stats Overview
    ├── /recruiter/jobs        → All Job Posts
    ├── /recruiter/jobs/new    → Add New Job Post
    ├── /recruiter/jobs/:id/applicants → View & Filter Candidates
    └── /recruiter/shortlisted → Shortlisted Candidates

